@page "/"

<PageTitle>Evan Kelly</PageTitle>

<main>
  <!--Sliding box background-->
  <div class="bg"></div>
  <div class="bg bg2"></div>
  <div class="bg bg3"></div>

  <div class="intro-text">
    <h1>Hi, I'm <span class="text-highlight">Evan</span>. I'm a software developer and I create responsive applications, like this website!</h1>
    <h2>Made With</h2>
    <div class="logos">
      <div class="logo logo1">
        <img src="/images/blazor.svg" />
        <h3>Blazor</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="logo logo2">
        <img src="/images/html5.svg" />
        <h3>HTML</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="logo logo3">
        <img src="/images/css3.svg" />
        <h3>CSS</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="logos logos2">
      <div class="logo logo4">
        <img src="/images/webAssembly.svg" />
        <h3>WebAssembly</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="logo logo5">
        <img src="/images/c-sharp.png" />
        <h3>C#</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="logo logo6">
        <img src="/images/dotnet.png" />
        <h3>.Net6</h3>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="projects-container">
    <h2>My Work</h2>

    <div class="page-height container-one">
      <article class="project-container code-editor">
        <div class="text">
          <div class="title">
            <h3>Code Editor</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>WinForms</li>
              <li>C#</li>
              <li>.NET 4.8</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p>
          A light-weight code editor built with WinForms and Visual Studio. Open folders, modify and save files and edit multiple documents concurrently.
          Other features include scrolling line-counts, context menus, and syntactical highlighting.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="image-links">
          <div class="buttons">
           <button id="project1-source">Source</button>
           <button id="project1-more">More</button>
          </div>
          <img id="code-editor"
               src="/images/projects/codeeditor.jpg"
               alt="WinForms based Code Editor" />
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="page-height container-two">
      <article class="project-container unity-game">
        <div class="title">
          <h3>2D Physics Game</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Unity Engine</li>
            <li>C#</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p>
        Infinite procedural generation, chunk management, occlusion culling, 2D newtonian physics, and a heavy emphasis on object-oriented design. Players try to travel the furthest and
        get the highest score.
        </p>
        <div class="image-links">
        <div class="buttons">
          <button id="project1-play">Play</button>
          <button id="project1-source">Source</button>
          <button id="project1-more">Learn More</button>
        </div>
        <img id="video-game" src="/images/projects/videogame.jpg" alt="WinForms based Code Editor" />
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="page-height container-three">
      <article class="project-container unity-game">
      <div class="title">
        <h3>Client Website</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Blazor</li>
          <li>C#/Javascript</li>
          <li>HTML/CSS</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p>
        Infinite procedural generation, chunk management, occlusion culling, 2D newtonian physics, and a heavy emphasis on object-oriented design. Players try to travel to furthest and
        get the highest score.
      </p>
      <div class="image-links">
        <div class="buttons">
          <button id="project1-source">Source</button>
          <button id="project1-more">More</button>
        </div>
        <img id="video-game" src="/images/projects/videogame.jpg" alt="WinForms based Code Editor" />
      </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="about-container">
      <div class="title">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <img id="pfp" src="/images/pfp.jpg"/>
      </div>

      <div class="introduction">
        <p>I've spent my whole life obsessed with technology. I started teaching myself programming in highschool, back in 2015. Learning Javascript and C#, I was passionate about making games as a creative outlet, but never made anything more than prototypes.
          I always gravitated to C# for its static/strong typing, and today have throughly immersed myself in the .NET ecosystem.
        </p>
        <p>
          Spending my free time doing graphics design and videography work for some extra money, I really began developing my eye for the aesthetic, and graphics design principals have bled their way into all facets of my work. No stranger to content management systems like Wix, I have made a dozen websites over the years, personal and professional.
        </p>
        <p>
          Now I use a combination .NET and Javascript to create responsive software aplications for web and native. I will be studying my Bachelor of Computer Science at Griffith University in 2023.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="contact-container">
      <div class="title">
        <h2>Contact Me</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer> 
      <div class="links">
        <img src="~/images/github.svg" alt="Website source code" />
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</main>